<section id="fs-idm209762880" class="questions">
<exercise id="fs-idm221192400">
<problem id="fs-idm214950192">
<para id="fs-idm196544720"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68072"/>What is the direct labor rate variance?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm215132976">
<para id="fs-idm177872912">A direct labor rate variance is the actual rate paid being different from the standard rate.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm207781424">
<problem id="fs-idm200558064">
<para id="fs-idm215424176"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68072"/>What is the direct labor time variance?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idm189578912">
<problem id="fs-idm199601424">
<para id="fs-idm210195936"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68072"/>What are some possible causes of a direct labor rate variance?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm159508960">
<para id="fs-idm214314480">Employees have a different level of experience than standards; the labor market is tighter or looser than expected; contract renegotiation.</para>
</solution>
