<exercise id="fs-idm217302608">
<problem id="fs-idm177484784">
<para id="fs-idm176767872"><link class="lo-reference" document="m68072"/>How is the total direct labor variance calculated?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm215909632">
<para id="fs-idm162366000">Total direct labor variance = (Actual hours × Actual rate) – (Standard hours × Standard rate) or the total direct labor variance is also found by combining the direct labor rate variance and the direct labor time variance.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
